Class JavaOps

java.lang.Object
io.github.eutro.wasm2j.ops.JavaOps
public class JavaOps extends Object
A collection of Ops and OpKeys that exist only in Java IR.

  • Field Details

    • INTRINSIC

      public static final UnaryOpKey<IntrinsicImpl> INTRINSIC
      Effect: an intrinsic instruction, implemented in Java code.

    • TABLESWITCH

      public static final SimpleOpKey TABLESWITCH
      Control: an Opcodes.TABLESWITCH instruction. With n-1 jump targets, the first n-1 correspond to keys [0, n-1). The last is the default branch.

    • LOOKUPSWITCH

      public static final UnaryOpKey<int[]> LOOKUPSWITCH
      Control: an Opcodes.LOOKUPSWITCH instruction. The argument corresponds to each jump target's key, with the last block the default branch.

    • TRY

      public static final UnaryOpKey<Type> TRY
      Control: introduce a try block, "jumps" to the first target in the case of an exception in its second block.

    • CATCH

      public static final UnaryOpKey<Type> CATCH
      Effect: pops the exception from the stack. Must be the first instruction in its block.

    • THIS

      public static final Op THIS
      Effect: loads the implicit receiver of a method.

    • DROP

      public static final Op DROP
      Effect: ignores its argument.

    • PUT_FIELD

      public static final UnaryOpKey<JClass.JavaField> PUT_FIELD
      Effect: set the given field on its first argument, or statically with only one argument.

    • BR_COND

      public static final UnaryOpKey<JavaOps.JumpType> BR_COND
      Control: jump conditionally. The first target is the one taken if the condition holds, the second is the fallthrough.

    • SELECT

      public static final UnaryOpKey<JavaOps.JumpType> SELECT
      Effect: check the third argument, if it is true, returns the first argument, otherwise the second.

    • BOOL_SELECT

      public static final UnaryOpKey<JavaOps.JumpType> BOOL_SELECT
      Effect: returns true if the condition holds, false otherwise.

    • ARRAY_GET

      public static final SimpleOpKey ARRAY_GET
      Effect: get an array's nth element. Arguments in that order.

    • ARRAY_SET

      public static final SimpleOpKey ARRAY_SET
      Effect: set an array's nth element to a value. Arguments in that order.
